        textEn: 'Denmark provides financial support to many of the world\'s poorest countries. This support is called international development cooperation. Denmark is one of few countries in the world that meets the UN\'s target that countries should give 0.7 percent of gross national income (GNI) in development aid. In 2025, this corresponds to approximately 22 billion kroner.',
